In https://github.com/rust-lang/git2-rs/pull/1241, the `StringArray` iterator was changed from returning `Option<&str>` to `Result<Option<&str>>`. I think it should instead have been changed to `Result<&str>`. The inner `Option` is unnecessary because it should only ever be None if there is a bug in the iterator implementation. This results in an unnecessary unwrap for the caller. I think the iterator should be:

```rust
    type Item = Result<&'a str, Error>;
    fn next(&mut self) -> Option<Result<&'a str, Error>> {
        self.range.next().map(|i| self.arr.get(i).transpose().unwrap())
    }
```

