## Feature Description

The Vercel AI SDK supports MCP server connections for tool execution. There's no built-in way to verify whether an MCP server is trustworthy before making tool calls. For production AI applications, this is a security gap.

## Proposed Solution

Integrate behavioral trust scoring via the [Dominion Observatory API](https://dominionobservatory.com) to verify MCP servers before tool execution. The API provides trust scores (0.0-1.0) based on behavioral analysis of 14,820+ MCP servers.

```typescript
async function verifyMcpServer(serverUrl: string, threshold = 0.7) {
  const resp = await fetch(
    `https://dominionobservatory.com/api/trust?url=${encodeURIComponent(serverUrl)}`
  );
  const data = await resp.json();
  if (data.trust_score < threshold) {
    throw new Error(`MCP server trust ${data.trust_score} below threshold`);
  }
  return data;
}

// Verify before connecting AI SDK to MCP tools
const trust = await verifyMcpServer("https://mcp-server.example.com");
console.log(`Trust: ${trust.trust_score} | SLA: ${trust.sla_grade}`);
```

## Why This Matters for AI SDK

Production AI apps built with the AI SDK need trust guarantees:
- Prevents supply chain attacks via compromised MCP servers
- Blocks data exfiltration through malicious tool calls
- Ensures SLA compliance for production deployments

## Additional Context

- API docs: https://dominionobservatory.com
- Free tier: 50 queries/day
- GitHub: https://github.com/sgdata-io/dominion-observatory
- Covers 14,820+ MCP servers with behavioral trust scoring and SLA grades

